Data mining and R language

What is data mining?

  • Discovery of new patterns

    • Cluster analysis
    • Anomaly detection
    • Rule mining
    • Regression
    • Summarization

What is not data mining?

  • Data management
  • Data preprocessing
  • Transformation
  • Modeling / inference
  • Visualization

What is R language

  • Pros

    • Open source
    • Community of millions of users and growing
    • Zillion of packages
    • Supports C++, Java, etc.
    • CLI

  • Cons

    • Steep learning curve
    • In-memory

Crunching big data - MapReduce

You and your 9 best friends are at National library. You are given 1 million of books and you need to find how many books have a title longer than 255 symbols?

  • Divide randomly the books
  • Separately, find all books matching the criteria and count them
  • Get total answer

Feature selection

  • Basic features
    • source IP address
    • source port
    • destination IP address
    • destination port
    • protocol
    • flags
    • number of bytes
    • number of packets
  • Derived features
    • time-window
    • connection window based features
